    "Consequently this scenario replicates the current impasse and fails to offer a viable path for governance.Scenario 2: Disregarding the Economic dimension.",
    "In this scenario (see graphic 13) the configuration allows the formation of a broad coalition comprising LIBER, SOCD, LEFT.",
    "This coalition is viable since the state (l, γ) lies in the intersection of their projected aspiration sets.",
    "Importantly this coalition constitutes a winning majority under the new parliament composition, suggesting that the omission of economic cleavages could enable effective coalition-building on the base of shared societal and openness values.• LEFT (l, γ)• SOCD • CONS • LIBER • RIGHT (13)Scenario 3: Disregarding the Societal dimension.",
    "In this scenario (see Graphic 14) the coalition comprising LIBER, CONS, RIGHT is viable since the aspirations of the three parties agree on state (1, α), and it is winning in the new parliament.• LEFT • SOCD • CONS • LIB • RIGHT (2,γ) (2,β) ( 1, α), ( 1, β) ( 1, α), ( 2, α) (1,α) (1,α) (14)Note that under the Gallopolis Constitution the President has the last word in the decision process."
